

A man attacked a group of schoolchildren with a knife in northwest China, killing two of them and injuring three others plus their teacher, state media reported Thursday.

The man dashed towards the pupils and their teacher when they were about to cross the street in front of their school in the Xinjiang autonomous region on Wednesday afternoon, Xinhua news agency reported.

One pupil died on the spot and another died in hospital, it quoted police as saying, adding they were aged nine or 10 years old.

Another three children and the injured teacher were in stable condition, Xinhua reported.

Police arrested a 38-year-old man but said the motive for the attack was still unknown.

